Foot and mouth disease, Algeria
------------------------------
Information received on 7 Aug 2014 from Dr Ahmed Chawky Karim Boughalem, Directeur des Services Veterinaires, Services Veterinaires, Ministere de l'Agriculture et du Developpement Rural, Alger, Algeria

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 1
Date of start of the event: 23 Jul 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 25 Jul 2014
Report date: 7 Aug 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Aug 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1999
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (43)

[For detailed statistics and other information pertaining to each of the 43 new outbreaks in relation to cattle, sheep and goats, please refer to the full report at the above URL. The following (11) provinces are mentioned: Setif, Medea, Constantine, Bouira, Borgj Bou Arreridj, Bejaia, Djelfa, Tizi Ouzou, Batna, Alger and Blida. The report includes an interactive map showing the outbreaks. - Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 43
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1646 / 334 / 79 / 0 / 1567
Sheep / 183 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 183
Goats 10 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 10

Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, expressed in percentages)
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 20.29 / 4.80 / 23.65 / 100.00
Sheep / 0.00 / 0.00 / - / 100.00
Goats / 0.00 / 0.00 / - / 100.00

*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Illegal movement of animals

Epidemiological comments
Other control measures: - closing of livestock markets in all wilayahs in the country, - ban on movement of animals at national level, - stamping out of all animals in the outbreaks, - investigations strengthened.

Control measures
Measures applied: Stamping out, Movement control inside the country, Screening, Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s).

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / Non-structural protein ELISA / 28 Jul 2014 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

