******
[3] French alertness
Date: Fri 8 Aug 2014
Source: Paysan-Breton [in French, machine trans. summarised, edited]
http://www.paysan-breton.fr/article/15432/alerte-fievre-aphteuse,-la-maladie-s%92installe-au-maghreb.html


Farmers are advised to make sure that outsiders entering their holdings clean and disinfect their shoes. Preferably, disposable shoe-covers should be supplied to visitors. Animal breeders are being updated about the main symptoms of FMD and urged to call their vets to examine any suspected case, "the visits to be supported by the state."

In addition, vehicles coming from or transiting through the infected countries should not enter the premises; the supply of forage, straw and litter from these countries is banned.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

